      "message": "whether or not to include the surrounding \"if\" test is dependent on the amount of work that has to occur when constructing the message to log.  If we were using slf4j, then we could use \"{}\" place-holders and be fine, but since we're not, we have to consider what's happening in the string concatenation.  In this case, how much work is done in workflowRequest.toString() and in ObjectUtils.toString()?  If very little, then it's fine to remove the \"if\" test.",
